You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, and Tailwind, Clerk Auth integration, database integration, and Framer Motion.

Code Style and Structure
Write concise, technical TypeScript code with accurate examples.
Use functional and declarative programming patterns and avoid classes.
Prefer iteration and modularization over code duplication.
Use descriptive variable names with auxiliary verbs (e.g., isLoading, hasError).
Structure files: exported components, subcomponents, helpers, static content, types.
Naming Conventions
Use lowercase with dashes for directories (e.g., components/auth-wizard).
Name components like new-component.tsx.
Favor named exports for components.
TypeScript Usage
Use TypeScript for all code and prefer interfaces over types.
Avoid enums and use maps instead.
Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces.
Syntax and Formatting
Use the "function" keyword for pure functions.
Avoid unnecessary curly braces in conditionals and use concise syntax for simple statements.
Use declarative JSX.
Error Handling and Validation
Prioritize error handling: handle errors and edge cases early.
Use early returns and guard clauses.
Implement proper error logging and user-friendly messages.
Use Zod for form validation.
Model expected errors as return values in Server Actions.
Use error boundaries for unexpected errors.
UI and Styling
Use Shadcn UI, Radix, and Tailwind Aria for components and styling.
Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS and use a mobile-first approach.
Performance Optimization
Minimize 'use client', 'useEffect', and 'setState' and favor React Server Components (RSC).
Wrap client components in Suspense with fallback.
Use dynamic loading for non-critical components.
Optimize images: use WebP format, include size data, implement lazy loading.
Key Conventions
Use 'nuqs' for URL search parameter state management.
Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, FID).
Limit 'use client' and use only for Web API access in small components.
Favor server components and Next.js SSR.
Avoid data fetching or state management.
Follow Next.js docs for Data Fetching, Rendering, and Routing.
Project Organization
Place both /app and /components folders under /src.
Maintain a clear and organized project structure.
Separate application logic (/src/app) and UI components (/src/components).
Use a modular approach for scalability and readability.
Components Organization
By Type: Group components like forms, buttons, layout elements, etc.
By Feature: Group components related to specific features or domains.
Example:

/src/components
├── /ui
│   ├── /Button
│   ├── /Modal
│   └── /Card
├── /forms
│   ├── /TextField
│   └── /Select
└── /layout
    ├── /Navbar
    └── /Footer


Private Components: Create _components folders within relevant /app subdirectories.
Shared Components: Store reusable components in /src/components.
